<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Britain-Horse,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Runaway horse injures 15 in bolt through town</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLEY, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A runaway horse that threw its young
rider bolted through this market town in northeastern England
Saturday and injured 15 people before it collided with a car and
was killed, police reported.
   They said three of the injured were hospitalized.
   The police report said a 15-year-old girl was riding the horse
on an exercise area in Beverley, near Hull, when it threw her and
galloped wildly through the narrow streets crowded with shoppers
before it ran into a car.,
   Most of of the injured were treated and released but a
9-year-old boy and two women, 45 and 60, were admitted to
hospitals, according to police.
</TEXT>
