<2ND_LINE>AM-Canada-Plane,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Searchers Find Wreckage Of Canadian Fighter Jet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COMOX, British Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The wreckage of a Canadian
fighter jet that disappeared while searching for a fishing boat was
found Saturday in a heavily wooded area on northern Vancouver
Island.
   The pilot of the CF-18 fighter, 27-year-old Capt. Michael
Erickson of Delta, did not survive the Tuesday crash, said Maj.
Robin Alford of the Rescue Coordination Center in Victoria.
   The body had not been recovered by late Saturday.
   Alford said the plane was discovered Saturday afternoon by a
search and rescue aircraft. The jet had crashed in a heavily wooded
area of Brooks Peninsula off the northwest coast of Vancouver
Island.
   It had been searching for a fishing boat that had been reported
missing in the area. The boat later returned to port.
   Alford said a military board of investigation was to be flown to
the site Sunday.
</TEXT>
