<HEAD>Retired Congressman John H. Dent Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENSBURG, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Retired U.S. Rep. John H. Dent, who
served in Congress for 20 years, has died of heart and kidney
failure after a long illness. He was 80 years old.
   Dent died early Saturday at Jeannette District Memorial Hospital
in Jeannette.
   The Democratic politician retired from the House of
Representatives in 1978 after representing western Pennsylvania's
21st Congressional District for two decades.
   Before winning election to Congress, Dent served in the state
Legislature, winning election to the Pennsylvania House of
Representatives in 1934 and to the state Senate in 1936, according
to his family.
   A Mass of Christian Burial will be held Tuesday at Blessed
Sacrament Cathedral in Greensburg. Interment will be private.
