<2ND_LINE>AM-Fugitive Shot,0357</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>FBI Ends 19-Hour Standoff By Gunning Down Federal Fugitive</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPERRYVILLE, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An FBI marksman ended an 19-hour siege
Sunday by killing a Connecticut fugitive who had been lured out of
a farmhouse where he was holding his 3-year-old son and the child's
mother, authorities said.
   A single shot felled Charles A. Leaf II, 30, as he ran from the
house to a nearby FBI helicopter, said agent Terry T. O'Connor. He
was holding the woman, Cheryl Hart, 27, and their 3-year-old son,
Charles Leaf III, at gunpoint, O'Connor said.
   Leaf was accused of kidnapping the two April 2 from their
Trumbull, Conn., home.
   Ms. Hart and the boy were shaken but uninjured in the shooting,
which occurred shortly after 3 p.m., O'Connor said. Leaf was
pronounced dead on arrival at the University of Virginia Medical
Center.
   Trumbull police Capt. Frederick Nacovitch described Leaf as a
construction worker who moved from place to place and had a history
of domestic violence involving Ms. Hart.
   Authorities here began looking for Leaf after finding his 1973
Chevrolet April 3 in a remote area of Rappahannock County, about 50
miles west of Washington, D.C.
   O'Connor said authorities intensified the search Saturday night
when evidence was found indicating Leaf may have been in a barn
adjacent to a farmhouse.
   ``Agents entered the farmhouse shortly before 8 p.m. Saturday
and were immediately confronted by Leaf,'' O'Connor said. Leaf was
armed with a 9mm rifle and was holding the woman and child in an
upstairs bedroom.
   As authorities negotiated with Leaf over the hours, he fired
three shots from the rifle, but did not strike anyone, O'Connor
said.
   ``Leaf repeatedly threatened to kill the woman and child as well
as the FBI agents,'' O'Connor added.
   Leaf eventually was persuaded to leave the farmhouse and go to
the waiting helicopter, but was shot before he got to the craft,
said O'Connor. He declined to give details such as what might have
been promised Leaf to get him to leave the house or how far the
helicopter was from the house.
</TEXT>
