<HEAD>Man, Two Women Found Stabbed to Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three people were stabbed to death Sunday
while a 98-year-old man slept a floor below, police said.
   A relative found the bodies of Dorothy Sewell, 64; her nephew,
Tyrone Mason, 33; and his 40-year-old girlfriend, whose name was
not released, on the second floor of the house about 10:30 a.m.,
police said.
